                                  REQUIREMENTS

You will need the DBus, GLib and DBus-GLib libraries.
On Debian-based systems these are available in the following packages:

* libdbus-1-3
* libglib2.0-0 (>= 2.16)
* libdbus-glib-1-2

                               BUILD REQUIREMENTS

You will need the DBus, GLib and DBus-GLib development libraries and headers.
Additionally, you will need the gettext tools.
On Debian-based systems these are available in the following packages:

* libdbus-1-dev
* libglib2.0-dev (>= 2.16)
* libdbus-glib-1-dev
* gettext

                                  INSTALLATION

Just type "make", followed by "make install". This will install all the
necessary files in your home directory. Other directories can be specified by
calling make with the prefix variable, for example, "make prefix=/usr install".

